he handler doesn't check for the `run` key at all, which is what script steps actually use. So I need to handle three cases: the `run` key for scripts, inline `prompt` text as a fallback when it's not a file reference, and the existing `file(\"...\")` syntax for prompts. I'm noticing an inconsistency in how the different config keys handle file references versus inline content. The `prompt` case tries to read a file but doesn't fall back to writing the inline text if it fails, while the `script` case properly falls back to the raw content. I need to fix the `prompt` case to match that pattern, and I also realize the `run` key handler is missing entirely from this section. I'm seeing the issues now—the prompt fallback isn't being written when file reads fail, and I'm missing the `run` key that the DSL actually uses for script steps. I need to add the fallback for inline prompt text and handle the `run` key with the same file-reading pattern as the other cases.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6157,"cache_read_input_tokens":44511,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6157,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36334803-23cc-465d-b4ed-5517c3e5b5e4","uuid":"38025912-7d35-4665-a5ff-f8e9986aa61d"}
